---
import Section from '../shared/Section.astro';
import SectionTitle from '../shared/SectionTitle.astro';
import Card from '../shared/Card.astro';
---

<Section>
  <SectionTitle label="AI-native architecture">
    Built for AI from the ground up
  </SectionTitle>

  <div class="reveal-children grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
    <Card>
      <div class="mb-4 font-mono text-2xl text-accent">{ }</div>
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary">Structured CRDs</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        Every component exposes typed Kubernetes Custom Resource Definitions. Specter reads configuration as typed data, not raw text. Machine-parseable by design.
      </p>
    </Card>

    <Card>
      <div class="mb-4 font-mono text-2xl text-accent">⊕</div>
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary">Unified OTel telemetry</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        All components emit metrics, logs, and traces via OpenTelemetry. Specter correlates signals across the entire stack in one query.
      </p>
    </Card>

    <Card>
      <div class="mb-4 font-mono text-2xl text-accent">◈</div>
      <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-text-primary">Pre-built semantic knowledge</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        Specter knows every CRD schema, integration dependency, failure mode, upgrade path, and compliance mapping. Before it starts. Not learned at runtime.
      </p>
    </Card>
  </div>

  <!-- Comparison row -->
  <div class="mt-12 reveal">
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-border-primary">
            <th class="py-4 pr-4 text-left font-medium text-text-tertiary"></th>
            <th class="py-4 px-4 text-left font-medium text-red-400">AI-bolted (competitors)</th>
            <th class="py-4 pl-4 text-left font-medium text-accent">AI-native (OpenOva)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-text-secondary">
          <tr class="border-b border-border-primary/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-text-primary">Context sent to LLM</td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4 text-red-400/80">Raw logs, unstructured configs, error dumps</td>
            <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-accent/80">Typed CRD state, correlated OTel signals</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-border-primary/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-text-primary">Speed</td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4 text-red-400/80">Slow (massive context window)</td>
            <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-accent/80">Fast (surgical context)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-border-primary/50">
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-text-primary">Cost</td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4 text-red-400/80">Expensive (many tokens)</td>
            <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-accent/80">Cheap (minimal tokens)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-medium text-text-primary">Accuracy</td>
            <td class="py-3 px-4 text-red-400/80">Low (noise drowns signal)</td>
            <td class="py-3 pl-4 text-accent/80">High (structured signal, no noise)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-6 text-center text-sm text-text-tertiary">
      Token efficiency is the economic moat. You cannot retrofit AI-manageability onto a platform that wasn&rsquo;t designed for it.
    </p>
  </div>
</Section>
